Job Description
Our Client is one of Asia’s largest energy investors. At this crucial time of expansion, they are looking to bring on an outstanding Private Equity Analyst to Director level top tier candidates to further grow their coverage in Indonesia and across the SEA.
Key Responsibilities:
•Identify, develop and maintain key relationships throughout Indonesia
•Responsible for mapping key Indonesian relationship and points of influence which span all market stakeholders
•Perform in-depth research and present (both written and orally) on the following:
-On the fundamentals of potential investments and investment partners
-General industry, sector and regulatory research to assist in the identification of opportunities
•Support deal execution including financial analysis, due diligence, documentation and financing
•Oversee extensive financial modelling and quantitative analysis on investment targets
Skills
• Significant transaction experience in evaluating, financing and/or undertaking due diligence for investment in the energy and infrastructure sectors in Indonesia
• A must to have excellent written and oral communication skills in Bahasa Indonesia and English
• Strong academic qualifications in math’s, actuarial studies, engineering or finance
• Strong Excel skills and be capable of building and operating all aspects of investment and asset management financial models and PowerPoint skills
• Exceptional presentation, interpersonal and leadership skills and the ability to confidently interact with senior management, investors and peers
•
Strong project management and organization skills, with clear understanding of meeting milestones and deadlines.
Qualifications:
Applicants must possess the following:
• Must be tertiary qualified and have at least 5-7 years? Work experience in a top tier international bank, investment bank, private equity firm or law firm specializing in energy, infrastructure, corporate finance, M&A; or structured finance
• Fluent in Bahasa Indonesia and English
Spencer Ogden is acting as an Employment Agency in relation to this vacancy.
Qualifications
Bachelors Degree or equivalent
